    • findDetached

      public T findDetached(Object id)
      Finds an entity by its primary key and detaches it from the persistence context.

      This method retrieves an entity from the database based on the provided `id`. After retrieval, the entity is detached from the persistence context. This means that subsequent changes to the entity will not be tracked or automatically persisted to the database. It is useful when you need to work with an entity outside the scope of a transaction without affecting the database state.

      Specified by:
      findDetached in interface AbstractDao<T extends AbstractModel<?>>
      Parameters:
      id - The primary key of the entity to retrieve.
      Returns:
      The detached entity, or `null` if no entity with the given `id` exists.

    • createQuery

      protected javax.persistence.Query createQuery(String select, String alias, String whereClause)
      Creates a query with the specified entity alias and where clause

      For example, invoking 

                      createQuery("select entity.id" "entity", "entity.propertyName like :propertyValue");

      would create query: 

                      SELECT entity.id FROM ModelClass AS entity WHERE entity.propertyName like :propertyValue
      Parameters:
      select - Select clause to be included in the query
      alias - Alias to be included in the query
      whereClause - Where clause to be included in the query
      Returns:
      Returns the query
